items.title: World central bank chiefs 'stand in solidarity' with US Fed chair Powell
items.description: Eleven central banks have backed Jerome Powell after the US launched a criminal investigation into the US Fed.

items.title: Senator Mark Kelly sues Defence Secretary Pete Hegseth over attempted demotion
items.description: The US senator and former Navy captain is contesting a move to review his retirement grade after he criticised the Trump administration.

items.title: Which countries do business with Iran  and what could US tariffs mean?
items.description: Donald Trump has announced a 25% tariff on countries trading with Iran after its deadly crackdown on anti-government protests.

items.title: Prosecutors seek death penalty for ex-South Korean president Yoon
items.description: Yoon is accused of leading an insurrection when he tried to impose martial law in 2024.

items.title: Le Pen hopeful appeal will allow her to run for French president
items.description: An appeal by France's far-right leader begins against a ruling banning her from running for public office for five years.
